  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving COVID 19 preparedness and prevention through integrated WASH interventions in Rural Damascus</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Oxfam is proposing a six-month rapid public health response to reach 32,500 people affected by the crisis in Rural Damascus Governorates. In addition to this, approximately 500,000 individuals will be reached by hygiene promotion messages through a media campaign in the whole country. The proposed action aims to improve the affected communities&apos; access to information on awareness in order to improve the prevention of COVID19 risks, and maintain key health and hygiene practices in the communities . A media campaign will be complimented by family hygiene kit distributions, cash for work activities relating to sterilizing high touch areas and message dissemination in the community, and improving access to solid waste management services. The project is aligned to the WASH Sector strategy for COVID Response it is a well defined response strategy suitable to the restricted movement situation and the existing security challenges (direct implementation through a competent media company, reliable and experienced volunteers and focal points). Oxfam will collaborate with relevant ministries, governorates amp directorates, the WASH sub-sectors and NGOs.</narrative>
  </description>
